The Small Business Administration announced Thursday it has reached its $349 billion lending limit and is no longer accepting applications.
McConnell said he had cleared the $250 billion package on the GOP side but that Democrats would have stopped it.
“Democrats would not let us reopen the program,” McConnell said.
(Photo: Susan Walsh, AP, File)“Democrats would not let us reopen the program,” McConnell said.
The Capitol is largely shuttered, requiring consensus from all sides for any legislation to pass, and top GOP leaders are vowing to stick closely to Trump’s request despite Democrats’ additional demands.